TY  - JOUR
T1  - Loosely Coupled Systems: A Reconceptualization
AU  - Orton, J. Douglas
AU  - Weick, Karl E.
Y1  - 1990/04/01
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1990.4308154
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1990.4308154
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 203
EP  - 223
VL  - 15
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Diverse applications of the concept of loose coupling are embodied in five recurring voices that focus separately on causation, typology, effects, compensations, and outcomes. Each has a tendency to drift away from a dialectical interpretation of loose coupling toward a unidimensional interpretation of loose coupling, thereby weakening the explanatory value of the concept. The authors first use the five voices to review the loose coupling literature and then to suggest more precise and more productive uses of the concept.
AB  - Diverse applications of the concept of loose coupling are embodied in five recurring voices that focus separately on causation, typology, effects, compensations, and outcomes. Each has a tendency to drift away from a dialectical interpretation of loose coupling toward a unidimensional interpretation of loose coupling, thereby weakening the explanatory value of the concept. The authors first use the five voices to review the loose coupling literature and then to suggest more precise and more productive uses of the concept.
